      <details>
        <summary>What does a 52-week high mean?</summary>
        <p>The 52-week high is the highest price at which a stock has traded during the previous year (52 weeks).</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Why is the 52-week high important?</summary>
        <p>It serves as a psychological indicator for investors and is often viewed as a key resistance level in technical analysis.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is it good to buy a stock at its 52-week high?</summary>
        <p>It can be. A stock hitting a 52-week high often shows strong momentum and bullish sentiment, but some investors fear buying at the peak before a pullback.</p>
      </details>
